author: Rob McBride
title: S Korea to hold first national election amid COVID-19 outbreak
description: Despite the health risks, there are indications the virus will not deter people from voting.
content:
South Korea is preparing to hold a national election, its first since the coronavirus outbreak began.
Despite the health risks, there are indications the virus will not deter people from voting.
Al Jazeera's Rob McBride reports from Seoul.
